Senator representing Plateau South in the National Assembly Prof Nora Ladi Daduut has congratulated Governor Simon Lalong on his 59th birthday anniversary. She said that “I want to use this opportunity to thank his Excellency Governor Simon Lalong for his support and to say that I would always support his political aspiration, I would always remain grateful to Gov Lalong for his support at all times. I am and ardent supporter of Governor Lalong and would support him always. -Advertisement- In a statement made available to newsmen in Jos on Wednesday, Senator Daduut said “Governor Lalong who is our leader is a gentleman and visionary leader who has over time shown his unalloyed commitment to the betterment of his people and continues to lead as a democrat and an unrepentant optimist.” She lauded Lalong’s commitment to the development of Plateau State and the country at large. Daduut further described Gov Lalong as a bridge-builder who has been working to enthrone peace and take the State to a higher height. “Governor Lalong who is also the Chairman of the Northern Governors’ Forum is a committed patriot and a bridge-builder who has contributed immensely to the growth and development of Plateau. He is patriotic, purposeful, dedicated and committed to issues that affect the country. Senator Daduut acknowledged the impactful programmes of the Simon Lalong -led government, especially the construction of the British American flyover bridge and several other projects. POLL “I wish you excellent health and God’s continued guidance in the years ahead. Senator Daduut prayed to God Almighty to continue to grant Lalong the wisdom and strength required to fulfill his desire for a prosperous and peaceful Plateau.